getCurrentTransaction

IDataTransaction getCurrentTransaction()
Returns the current active transaction, which is an instance of IDataMultiUpdateTransaction.

Specified by:
getCurrentTransaction in interface IDataTableRecord
Returns:
Returns the current active transaction or null, if no current active transaction exists, e.g. the record has already been committed.
See Also:
IDataMultiUpdateTransaction

getAssociatedTransaction

IDataMultiUpdateTransaction getAssociatedTransaction()
Returns the associated active transaction.

Note: In contrast to getCurrentTransaction() this method always returns a transaction, i.e. even if the transaction is not active (closed) anymore. This is useful to obtain completion error information by means of IDataMultiUpdateTransaction.hasCompletionErrors() or IDataMultiUpdateTransaction.getCompletionError(IDataRecord).

Returns:
Returns the associated active transaction.
See Also:
IDataMultiUpdateTransaction

getUnderlyingRecords

java.util.List getUnderlyingRecords()
Returns the underlying table records which are involved by this multiple update record instance.

Returns:
the list of underlying table records, i.e. instances of IDataTableRecord
